channel.description: Ok so I'm trying to use runeagent and keep running into an error every server I try it on. "ReferenceError: "stream" is not defined in nashorn:mozilla_compat.js at line number 67" I've looked all over the silabsoft forums and can't figure this out. I think I have the config file setup wrong. I tryed watching this video http://silabsoft.org/forum/discussion/175/identifying-the-stream-class-its-methods-from-the-bytecode-in-obfuscated-clients but I don't understand what I am suppose to be looking for. [spoiler]my config file [[img]http://i.imgur.com/fgZbad2.png?1[/img] http://i.imgur.com/fgZbad2.png?1 img url since the picture above isn't the whole picture[/spoiler] Any help would be much appreciated.

item.description:
@mrbad23 wrote:

[quote=“Miss Silabsoft, post:2, topic:551681”]the new Runetek4CLientTransformer needs the name of the client class and the name of the isaaccipher class

the Classmodifier of the bytestream needs the name of the streamclass

the methods wrappers are the names of the methods to wrap and their signatures.[/quote]
Thanks! I’ll see if I can get this to work then
EDIT:
I tried to find out which one was the stream class by going through each file and looking at the bytecode but couldnt figure out which one was the stream class
